#X text 34 19 The last example advanced a bit and showed a random modulation of pitch along with random modulation of amplitude. No need to repeat it. But instead of using [rescale~] to set the output range we do it differently in here and simply sum the pitch frequency value in MIDI to an oscillator output. The oscillator amplitude sets the modulation range in semitones. A 0.25 value means an eight tone up and down \, so we have a quarter tone vibrato. You could have a ramp noise instead and also modulate the signal in the frequency realm in hertz instead., f 63;
